Nintendo President's Stock Sale
Mr. Yamauchi remains Nintendo's leading shareholder, with
about 11%, the spokeswoman said.
   In January, a group led by Mr. Yamauchi but made up of
mainly U.S. investors made a $100 million bid to buy the
financially troubled baseball club, stirring controversy in
the U.S. Mr. Yamauchi is to put up 60% of the total
investment.